   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Credit-Card Fraud Detection \u2014 Critical Reproduction & Stress-Test\n",
    "\n",
    "**Course:** Data Science in Cyber \u2014 Dr. Uri Itai  \n",
    "**Source under evaluation:** `shakiliitju/Credit-Card-Fraud-Detection-Using-Machine-Learning`  \n",
    "**Dataset:** Kaggle / ULB credit-card fraud dataset (Dal Pozzolo et al.) \u2014 284,807 transactions, PCA-anonymised features.\n",
    "\n",
    "The source builds a KNN / Decision-Tree classifier and reports **~100% accuracy** as success. This notebook\n",
    "reproduces that result on the real data and then critically tests three claims: (1) that accuracy is a meaningful\n",
    "measure here, (2) that the preprocessing is sound, and (3) that the model actually detects fraud rather than\n",
    "exploiting the overwhelming class imbalance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Environment setup (Colab / fresh checkout)\n",
    "\n",
    "The notebook reads `DataFiles/creditcard.csv.gz` with a **relative path**, so the repo must be present in the\n",
    "working directory. On a clean environment (e.g. Colab) the cell below clones the repo and `cd`s into it; run\n",
    "from a local clone it detects `DataFiles/` and does nothing.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **One-time edit:** after you create the GitHub repo, set `REPO_URL` below to its URL."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Colab / fresh-environment setup -------------------------------------\n",
    "import os, subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    REPO_URL = "https://github.com/Yarinys/data-science-cyber-class-project"
    "REPO_DIR = REPO_URL.rstrip('/').split('/')[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(\"DataFiles\"):\n",
    "    if not os.path.isdir(REPO_DIR):\n",
    "        subprocess.run([\"git\", \"clone\", \"--depth\", \"1\", REPO_URL], check=True)\n",
    "    os.chdir(REPO_DIR)\n",
    "\n",
    "assert os.path.exists(\"DataFiles/creditcard.csv.gz\"), \\\n",
    "    \"DataFiles/creditcard.csv.gz not found - check the clone step / REPO_URL above.\"\n",
    "print(\"Working directory:\", os.getcwd())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Imports, one fixed random seed for reproducibility, the data path, and a single `evaluate_model` helper so the\n",
    "metric-computing code is written once and reused for every model (no duplicated evaluation code)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\n",
    "                             fbeta_score, matthews_corrcoef, roc_auc_score,\n",
    "                             average_precision_score, confusion_matrix)\n",
    "\n",
    "SEED = 42\n",
    "np.random.seed(SEED)\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "DATA_PATH = "DataFiles/creditcard.csv",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate_model(name, model, X_tr, y_tr, X_te, y_te):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Fit a model and return the full classification metric suite as a dict.\n",
    "    Positive class = fraud (1). We report precision/recall/F-scores/MCC/PR-AUC\n",
    "    because accuracy alone is uninformative under extreme class imbalance.\"\"\"\n",
    "    model.fit(X_tr, y_tr)\n",
    "    pred = model.predict(X_te)\n",
    "    proba = model.predict_proba(X_te)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, \"predict_proba\") else pred\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"model\": name,\n",
    "        \"accuracy\":  accuracy_score(y_te, pred),\n",
    "        \"precision\": precision_score(y_te, pred, zero_division=0),\n",
    "        \"recall\":    recall_score(y_te, pred),\n",
    "        \"f1\":        f1_score(y_te, pred),\n",
    "        \"f2\":        fbeta_score(y_te, pred, beta=2),\n",
    "        \"mcc\":       matthews_corrcoef(y_te, pred),\n",
    "        \"roc_auc\":   roc_auc_score(y_te, proba),\n",
    "        \"pr_auc\":    average_precision_score(y_te, proba),\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
