   "source": [
    "## 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "\n",
    "The single most important fact about this dataset is its **extreme class imbalance**: fraud is ~0.17% of rows.\n",
    "In the real world phishing-style fraud genuinely is rare, so this prevalence is realistic (unlike an artificially\n",
    "balanced set). The consequence: a model can be ~99.8% *accurate* by never predicting fraud at all, so accuracy\n",
    "is the wrong yardstick. We keep that in mind throughout the EDA."
   ]
