   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Correlation analysis and choosing the right method.** We want the features most associated with the fraud\n",
    "label. The target `Class` is **binary** (0/1), so Pearson-with-a-binary-variable is exactly the **point-biserial\n",
    "correlation** \u2014 the standard measure of association between a continuous variable and a binary outcome. A natural\n",
    "instinct is to reach for **Spearman** (rank-based, robust to outliers), but it is the *wrong* choice here: with\n",
    "99.83% of rows tied at `Class = 0`, the target's ranks are dominated by one giant block of ties, which collapses\n",
    "every correlation toward zero. We show both measures side by side to make the point, then rank features by\n",
    "|point-biserial (Pearson)|. (This is the opposite of a dataset with ordinal/binary *features*, where Spearman\n",
    "would be the right call \u2014 the correct method depends on the data, not habit.)"
   ]
  },
