  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "The features are already numeric: `V1`-`V28` are PCA components (already centred and scaled by construction),\n",
    "and only `Amount` and `Time` sit on raw scales. Two engineering decisions matter for correctness:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Scaling belongs inside a pipeline.** Distance- and gradient-based models (KNN, logistic regression) need\n",
    "   features on comparable scales. The crucial point - and the source's mistake - is that the scaler must be fit\n",
    "   on the **training data only**. We wrap `StandardScaler` in a `Pipeline` with each such model, so the scaler\n",
    "   never sees the test set. (Random Forest and XGBoost are scale-invariant and need no scaling.)\n",
    "2. **No resampling before the split.** We do *not* oversample here. Resampling before splitting leaks synthetic\n",
    "   minority rows into the test set; imbalance is instead handled inside each model via class weights /\n",
    "   `scale_pos_weight`. (We test the resampling-leakage pitfall explicitly in the experiments.)\n",
    "\n",
    "We use one stratified 80/20 split so the tiny fraud class keeps the same proportion in train and test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
