    "transforms, so a log helps linear/distance models but not XGBoost. `Hour` carries a clear EDA signal yet barely\n",
    "moves PR-AUC, because the PCA components already encode most of the separable structure. The honest, *measured*\n",
    "conclusion is that feature creation aids understanding here more than performance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4-5. Model Training, Comparison & Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "We compare five models, all scored on the same held-out test set with the full metric suite:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **KNN (k=1)** - the source's model, but done correctly (scaler fit on training data only).\n",
    "- **Decision Tree** - the source's *second* model, default settings (no depth limit), which memorises the training data.\n",
    "- **Logistic Regression (balanced)** - a linear baseline with `class_weight='balanced'`, so the rare fraud class\n",
    "  is up-weighted in the loss instead of being ignored.\n",
    "- **Random Forest (balanced)** - a class-weighted ensemble of trees; scale-invariant.\n",
    "- **XGBoost (scale_pos_weight)** - gradient-boosted trees, positive class up-weighted by the imbalance ratio.\n",
    "\n",
    "For fraud, the metric that matters is **recall** (catching fraud) traded against **precision** (not drowning\n",
    "analysts in false alarms); we summarise that trade-off with **F2** (recall-weighted) and **PR-AUC**, not accuracy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Metric definitions\n",
    "\n",
    "With fraud as the positive class, a **false negative (FN)** is a missed fraud (direct loss) and a **false\n",
    "positive (FP)** is a blocked legitimate transaction (customer friction). We report and interpret:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Accuracy** = (TP+TN)/all - dominated by the legit majority here, so uninformative.\n",
    "- **Precision** = TP/(TP+FP) - of flagged transactions, how many were really fraud (false-alarm control).\n",
    "- **Recall (TPR)** = TP/(TP+FN) - of real frauds, how many we caught (miss control).\n",
    "- **F1** = harmonic mean of precision & recall; **F2** weights recall higher (missing fraud costs more).\n",
    "- **MCC** = balanced correlation over all four confusion-matrix cells; honest under imbalance.\n",
    "- **ROC-AUC** = threshold-free ranking quality, but insensitive to prevalence (can flatter rare-event models).\n",
    "- **PR-AUC** = area under precision-recall; reacts to imbalance, so it is our primary summary metric."
   ]
  },
